Find out how it started

* Did you know? The E-Summit at NIT Durgapur is recognized as the second largest entrepreneurship summit in Eastern India, attracting prominent entrepreneurs and celebrity speakers each year.

Celebrating Visionaries

Who has graced our stage?

Over the years, E-Summit has hosted an incredible array of thought leaders. From startup founders and tech visionaries to corporate leaders and innovative entrepreneurs - our stage has welcomed them all! Each speaker has brought unique insights, inspiring success stories, and invaluable knowledge, creating an unforgettable impact on our attendees.

2.

Inspiring theNext Generation

Who benefits from their wisdom?

Every aspiring entrepreneur, student, and innovator! Whether it's disruptive marketing tips, business growth strategies, or leadership lessons, our speakers cater to all. Bold risk-takers learn from fearless founders, while strategic thinkers gain insights from corporate leaders. At E-Summit, there’s inspiration for everyone

How to make the most of E-Summit?

No worries — we’ve got plenty of events to keep you hooked. The stage is set, the energy is electric — are you ready to ride the wave of innovation?

E-Talks

The centerpiece of E-Summit, brings visionary entrepreneurs and industry leaders to the stage. With past speakers like Prajakta Kohli (MostlySane), Prafull Billore (MBA Chaiwala), Iqlipse Nova (BigBrainCo), Ishan Sharma (MarkitUp), and Kiran Bedi, these sessions offer students priceless insights, inspiring stories, and expert advice on navigating the entrepreneurial journey.

Hello! We are...

Team EDC

“Entrepreneurship Development Cell (EDC) at NIT Durgapur started in 2015 as a modest initiative by a group of enterprising students aiming to foster a culture of innovation and entrepreneurship within the campus. Over time, this initiative gained momentum, evolving into a significant platform that nurtures entrepreneurial skills and connects students with industry leaders, investors, and successful entrepreneurs."

"Its flagship fest, E-Summit, has become one of the most prominent in Eastern India, comprising diverse events like E-Talks, Startup Expo, Internship Fair, among others. These initiatives provide students with opportunities to network, gain real-world insights, and transform their innovative ideas into viable business ventures. The cell's journey from a small student-led initiative to a leading entrepreneurial body reflects its unwavering commitment to promoting entrepreneurship and supporting the startup ecosystem both within and beyond the institute.”
